objects.moduledoc: Mix task to genereate `.yaml` file based on project files and functions `y/1`, `y/3`
Module to get translation in a language specified in config.
Module parse `.yaml` files and store translations in `ets` table, also contain functions to get translations from same `ets` table.
Exception raised when trying use `y/2` or `y/4` without `plug` dependency.
Exception raised when trying `get_plural!/1` for not defined language `behaviour` module.

objects.name: run
objects.doc:
Generate `.yaml` file based on project files and functions `y/1`, `y/3`.

Default create `schema.yaml` file and save in `priv/y18n`.

## Parameters
`mix y18n.fetch --lang="pl"` Create yaml file for specific language.

`mix y18n.fetch "priv/templates/**/*.eex"` Add directory to detect `y/1`, `y/3` functions.

objects.name: y
objects.doc:
Translate string from parameter to language specified in config.

## Examples
    iex> Orisons.Y18N.y("Hello world")
    "Witaj świecie"

objects.name: y
objects.doc:
Translate string from parameter to language from session stored in `Plug.Conn`.

## Examples
    iex> Orisons.Y18N.y(conn, "Hello world")
    "Witaj świecie"

objects.name: y
objects.doc:
Translate string from parameter to language specified in config with plural detection.

## Examples
    iex> Orisons.Y18N.y("%d apple", "%d apples", 3)
    "3 jabłka"

objects.name: y
objects.doc:
Translate string from parameter to language from session stored in `Plug.Conn`, with plural detection.

## Examples
    iex> Orisons.Y18N.y(conn, "%d apple", "%d apples", 3)
    "3 jabłka"

objects.doc:

objects.name: get_translation

objects.name: get_translation_plural

objects.name: get_plural
objects.doc:
Get plural module by language shortcut

## Example:

    iex> Orisons.Y18N.Plural.get_plural(:en)
    {:ok, Orisons.Y18N.Plural.En}

objects.name: get_plural!
objects.doc: Same as `Orisons.Y18N.Plural.get_plural/1`, but if language is not defined will throw `Orisons.Y18N.Plural.LanguageException`

objects.name: get_plural_count
objects.doc:
Determinates plural variant based on `count` and `lang`

## Example:

    iex> Orisons.Y18N.Plural.get_plural_count(1, :pl)
    "a"

objects.name: get_plurals
objects.doc: Keyword list of modules where key is language shortcut
